¬∂ ‚¶ä
  ‚Äñ The compact notation $y = Ax$ is sometimes called the
    ‚ù¨matrix form‚ù≠ of the $m$ linear equations and $A$ the
    ‚ù¨coefficient matrix‚ù≠. ‚¶â
‚¶â

¬∂ ‚¶ä
  ‚Äñ This notation suggests both algebraic and geometric
    interpretations of solving systems of linear equations. ‚¶â

  ‚Äñ The algebraic interpretation is that we are interested in
    the invertibility of the function $x \mapsto Ax$. ‚¶â

  ‚Äñ In other words, we are interested in the existence of an
    inverse element of $A$. ‚¶â

  ‚Äñ The geometric interpretation is that $A$ transforms the
    vector $x$. ‚¶â
‚¶â

